Key Match Events: Travis Head scored an unbeaten 154 and Marnus Labuschagne contributed 77 as Australia successfully chased down a formidable 316-run target to beat England by seven wickets
Australia reached 317-3 with six overs to spare after bowling England out for 315 in 49.4 overs
Adam Zampa took three for 49 on his 100th ODI
Marnus Labuschagne took three scalps for England
Pre-Game Insights: Chris Woakes suggested that England ‘did everything we said we were going to do’ and that they ‘went out there and scored quickly’ but ‘it wasn’t our day today’
Harry Brook said that ‘it probably went wrong at the toss when I batted first’ and that ‘we probably didn’t rotate spin well enough through the middle period’
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Brook suggested that ‘it’s a five-game series and four more to go’ and that they ‘move forward’ from this loss
Stuart Broad called Travis Head an ‘incredible player’ across all three formats
Ricky Ponting said that ‘Travis playing the way they did, Australia will be very happy with that’ and that ‘with no Starc or Hazelwood in the game, they managed things well’
Miscellaneous Highlights: Travis Head’s unbeaten 154 came off 129 balls with 20 fours and five sixes
Marnus Labuschagne contributed an unbeaten 77 in an unbroken 148-run stand with Head
Will Jacks took 0-25 in 6 overs for England
